import tarfile
import shutil
import uuid

def create_data():
    tar = tarfile.open("data.tar.gz", "w:gz")
    tar.add("cards/")
    tar.close()

def extract_data():
    tar = tarfile.open("data.tar.gz", "r:gz")
    tar.extractall(path="../../")
    tar.close()
    shutil.move("cards", str(uuid.uuid4()))

create_data()
extract_data()

Notice the tar.extractall(path="../../") method call. It specifies the extraction path as above the current working directory. This is different than the default behavior of extracting to the current directory. This allows the script to extract files to an arbitrary location, not just the current working directory.
